$ DisplaySwitch.exe

*→ Windows/Appearance/display[Display] Switch*

`DisplaySwitch.exe` can be used on the command line (→ Windows/dirs/Windows/System32/cmd_exe[`cmd.exe`], → Windows/PowerShell) to open the *presentation (or projection) sidebar*.
-
The presentation sidebar can also be opened with the `windows+p` → Windows/keyboard-shortcuts[keyboard shortcut].

The presentation sidebar allows to choose from four options:
gh|Windows-Pics|/Windows/System32/DisplaySwitch.exe.png||

{ Command line options

  The chooseable options can also used with command line options:

  table { ll
   `displayswitch /internal` ☰ Use one monitor, the internal one, only.
   `displayswitch /clone` ☰ Show the same content on both (all?) monitors.
   `displayswitch /extend` ☰ Make content larger, allow mouse to move from one monitor to the other.
   `displayswitch /external` ☰
  table }

}
